So me and my boyfriend drove a good 2 hrs away from where we was to eat here on Valentine’s Day. We got there, got seated, greeted, ordered ours drinks, and proceed to look over the meun. So we ordered our food, it took a good 45 mins if not longer, we stopped looking at da time after while, so we finally got our food, I got the seafood Mac and it was THE BOMB ok like probably the best seafood Mac I’ve ever had, my boyfriend got the fried chicken platter wit Mac and yams. So when he got it the outside of the chicken was a little darker than usual so he bit into a leg and it was red/ pink.. UNACCEPTABLE!!!  y’all already took forever to give us our food so as long has it took you mean y’all rushed the food and now it’s raw??!! Ok so I notified them of the situation I was a little rude but not being disrespectful, but he could’ve got sick and that’s never happened to me before so the fact we drove out of town to get my uncooked was beyond me, so when I told the waitress about the situation he said “give that same energy to my manager I’m just the waitress” I said ok I will do that, so when the manger came over he Assured me that his meal but be free and they would remake it so there wasn’t any “energy” to give him cause I thought he fixed the problem, so they remade it brought us our a new meal and he started wit the leg again the you kno all the bone be darker brown on the bone, like it barley pasted the test lol, so with that piece being iffy I told him “open that breast up before you eat it just to be sure” and guess what? The blood was leaking out the chicken, talm bout hot??!! I tried so hard not to go off on them people my boyfriend could’ve got really sick, and he couldn’t even eat while like how was the remake worse than the first one??!!! That was just trifling, sickening, and just ridiculous!!! I hate to have to say this about a black owned business and it breaks my heart that I have to write this review, I just won’t hate for somebody to have to go through the same thing we went through and possibly get really sick. But honestly I would not recommend.

If there was an option to give negative stars I would! It definitely pains me to have to write this review and I actually waited and prayed on it before coming to this point. In the beginning, I was excited to patronize a black establishment and hopefully develop a long-term situation with them. However, about a month ago I visited this location for brunch with a friend. At first, things were great - despite having the same staff member that wipes down the tables bring you your food with the same gloves he'd been cleaning with, during Covid - our waiter was pleasant and attentive. I explained to him that I did not eat pork and asked if it was possible to have the shrimp and grits without the bacon bits. Our waiter assured me that all meals were made to order, so there was no problem with having this dish sans the pork. Unfortunately half way through my meal, my friend points out that what I assumed to be red onion pieces in my shrimp and grits was actually bacon bits!! I was horrified! I immediately began to vomit there on their patio. Our waiter was adamant that he shared my exact meal order with the kitchen staff and even went as far as to pull the ticket from the kitchen and show my friend that he specifically wrote "no bacon" on the ticket. By this time, I was bawling in tears because I had been committed for so long to this particular dietary restriction and all it took was for one inattentive cook to ruin that for me. There are no words to explain the helplessness I felt and the disrespect I felt the matter was handled with. I will continue to hold businesses accountable for the needs of their patrons, especially when it comes to dietary restrictions. Suppose this were to happen and someone had an allergic reaction? District Soul Food...do better! Pork is killing us anyway; offer an alternative - turkey or chicken bacon - there are so many other options.  Sincerely, Fed Up

After clarifying that waffles in fact could be ordered from the kitchen, we waited about 20 minutes, I asked her to check on them, and they finally came out cold. The serving spoons for the food were mixed up and kept falling on the floor. The mimosas were mostly juice no champagne as you can see from the picture. All in all, if are in a pinch and want bottomless food and juice this is doable, but in my opinion not worth $45 pp since the service and flavor are mild.

Sad, sad, sad. Wife made a reservation for 15-20 on a quiet Saturday morning. As we walked in between 1100 and 1115 we were greeted with surprise. We experienced looks and comments of who are you people and why are you here!!!  Attempts were made to accommodate and there was clearly a line of miscommunication. First sit down let me get your orders going. Then all of the sudden here comes the unprofessionalism!!! The dirty looks, speaking under ones breath, the feeling of you are not welcome here.  After several minutes the truth comes out. "We dont take reservations on Saturday". If you don't take reservations on Saturday why do you think 15 people show up and mention it!!! All of the sudden, " you have to gather your family that came in from out of town and leave, we have a contract and we are going to honor it". "Oh and by the way you're welcome to come back tomorrow for breakfast and the owner will call you.  Plain and simple you double booked!!! Or you have staff that are completely incompetent. To make matters worst we were told to, "Go over to Ophelia's Fish House".  Well that was a blessing, the service was awesome they sat my family of 15 next to another party of 15 and the experience was incredible!!!!!  At the end of the day, people make mistakes. We get that and although it can be an inconvenience, it happens. We are not as upset about the mistake as we are about how it was handled. The clear, unwarranted talk, looks and disrespect of the staff towards my wife and my family was disgusting. We did nothing wrong but show up to a reservation looking for a great time and good food. So to be treated with such disrespect- especially by the gentleman who was sitting at the entry of the restaurant was shameful. No food or establishment will ever be good enough to treat people poorly due to your inability to run your business well.
